Pattern 1: Simple Filtering ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Question words
Find
Show
Employees older than 30
Customers from India
Use
SELECT ...
FROM table
WHERE condition;

Example

SELECT *
FROM Employee
WHERE salary > 50000;
Pattern 2: Remove Duplicates ⭐⭐⭐⭐

Question words

Unique
Distinct

Use

SELECT DISTINCT column
FROM table;
Pattern 3: Sorting ⭐⭐⭐⭐

Question words

Highest
Lowest
Latest
Earliest

Use

ORDER BY column DESC

or

ORDER BY column ASC
Pattern 4: Top N ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Question words

Highest salary
Top 5
Largest
Smallest

Use

ORDER BY salary DESC
LIMIT 5;

or

DENSE_RANK()
Pattern 5: Frequency Count ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Question words

Appears once
Number of employees
Count products
Frequency

Use

GROUP BY
COUNT()

Example

SELECT department,
COUNT(*)
FROM Employee
GROUP BY department;
Pattern 6: Filter Groups ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Question words

Departments with more than 5 employees
Numbers appearing once

Use

GROUP BY

HAVING

Example

GROUP BY department

HAVING COUNT(*) > 5
